    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and
        Camshaft - Removal - Camshaft Gear
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Camshaft Gear</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If required,
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_411.xml" xrefid="s1610">Measure Camshaft End Play</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s1610"/>.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f3350016509" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk03/k03005.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Camshaft gear and Cam Gear Puller</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For easier camshaft gear removal, remove the camshaft gear before removing the camshaft assembly,
                    upper idler, or lower idler gears.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para id="s1607" count="1">Install two claws of the
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_428.xml" xrefid="t335001603">Cam Gear Puller</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001603"/>
                into two holes of the camshaft gear.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Center the gear puller threaded shaft on the center of the camshaft and tighten shaft while
                firmly attaching puller claws on the camshaft gear.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Keep the Cam Gear Puller center shaft in line with the camshaft center line while removing the cam
                    gear.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the camshaft gear by rotating the gear puller center shaft in a continuous motion
                using a breaker bar, while holding the camshaft gear and Cam Gear Puller from rotating.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
